            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-34743",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "xz: XZ Utils: Denial of Service via buffer overflow in index decoding"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "XZ Utils provide a general-purpose data-compression library plus command-line tools. Prior to version 5.8.3, if lzma_index_decoder() was used to decode an Index that contained no Records, the resulting lzma_index was left in a state where where a subsequent lzma_index_append() would allocate too little memory, and a buffer overflow would occur. This issue has been patched in version 5.8.3."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-34743",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-34743\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: liblzma5\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-34743](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-34743)\nXZ Utils provide a general-purpose data-compression library plus command-line tools. Prior to version 5.8.3, if lzma_index_decoder() was used to decode an Index that contained no Records, the resulting lzma_index was left in a state where where a subsequent lzma_index_append() would allocate too little memory, and a buffer overflow would occur. This issue has been patched in version 5.8.3.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-34743**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|liblzma5||[CVE-2026-34743](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-34743)|\n\nXZ Utils provide a general-purpose data-compression library plus command-line tools. Prior to version 5.8.3, if lzma_index_decoder() was used to decode an Index that contained no Records, the resulting lzma_index was left in a state where where a subsequent lzma_index_append() would allocate too little memory, and a buffer overflow would occur. This issue has been patched in version 5.8.3."
