            {
              "id": "CVE-2025-15649",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "IO::Uncompress::Unzip versions before 2.215 for Perl propagate uncaugh ..."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "IO::Uncompress::Unzip versions before 2.215 for Perl propagate uncaught exception when parsing zip header with malformed DOS date.\n\n_dosToUnixTime() decodes the local-file-header last-modification date field and calls Time::Local::timelocal() without an eval guard. A header whose date field decodes to an out-of-range month, day, or hour causes timelocal() to die.\n\nThe exception propagates out of IO::Uncompress::Unzip-\u003enew($file) where callers expect undef plus $UnzipError."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-15649",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-15649\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: perl-base\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2025-15649](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-15649)\nIO::Uncompress::Unzip versions before 2.215 for Perl propagate uncaught exception when parsing zip header with malformed DOS date.\n\n_dosToUnixTime() decodes the local-file-header last-modification date field and calls Time::Local::timelocal() without an eval guard. A header whose date field decodes to an out-of-range month, day, or hour causes timelocal() to die.\n\nThe exception propagates out of IO::Uncompress::Unzip-\u003enew($file) where callers expect undef plus $UnzipError.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2025-15649**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|perl-base||[CVE-2025-15649](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-15649)|\n\nIO::Uncompress::Unzip versions before 2.215 for Perl propagate uncaught exception when parsing zip header with malformed DOS date.\n\n_dosToUnixTime() decodes the local-file-header last-modification date field and calls Time::Local::timelocal() without an eval guard. A header whose date field decodes to an out-of-range month, day, or hour causes timelocal() to die.\n\nThe exception propagates out of IO::Uncompress::Unzip-\u003enew($file) where callers expect undef plus $UnzipError."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "5.5",
                "tags": [
                  "vulnerability",
