            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-27171",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "zlib: zlib: Denial of Service via infinite loop in CRC32 combine functions"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "zlib before 1.3.2 allows CPU consumption via crc32_combine64 and crc32_combine_gen64 because x2nmodp can do right shifts within a loop that has no termination condition."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-27171",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-27171\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: zlib1g\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-27171](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-27171)\nzlib before 1.3.2 allows CPU consumption via crc32_combine64 and crc32_combine_gen64 because x2nmodp can do right shifts within a loop that has no termination condition.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-27171**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|zlib1g||[CVE-2026-27171](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-27171)|\n\nzlib before 1.3.2 allows CPU consumption via crc32_combine64 and crc32_combine_gen64 because x2nmodp can do right shifts within a loop that has no termination condition."
              },
              "properties": {
